data.title: Shadow Mountain Lookout
data.meta_description: National Park Service photograph of Shadow Mountain Lookout, circa 1955. Note the unprocessed stone masonry on the first two stories and the locally sourced evergreen beams on the top floor. The rustic qualities of the lookout dignify it as one of the best examples of the New-Deal-Era parkitecture in the country.
